    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Dec. 21. 1850</date>
            </p>
            <p>The <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dr. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My absence from home for more than a<lb/> week has deferred the
                accomplishment of my promise<lb/> until this time. I hasten to comply with the
                request<lb/> of your letter, which I find on my return to <placeName>New
                    York</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I was not aware of the publication of <persName>Mr.
                    Pey-<lb/>nado's</persName> letter in the Asmonean until informed by you.
                How<lb/> it could have been published, I cannot imagine un-<lb/>less through the
                agency of some one into whose hands the<lb/> manuscript has fallen since the meeting
                of Synod—for<lb/> on examining my papers I find that it was not<lb/> returned to me
                as Stated Clerk, by the committee &amp;<lb/> whom it and the numbers of the Occident
                were referred.<lb/> I will make inquiry and if possible ascertain in<lb/> what was
                the manuscript got into the hands of the<lb/> publisher of the Asmonean. Of one
                thing however<lb/> you may assure <persName>Mr. Peynado</persName>, that you did
                faithfully<lb/> transmit his manuscript to me, and that, after it<lb/> had been in
                my possession for several months it<lb/> was duly laid before the Synod. Until I
                read</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>your letter I certainly supposed that it had<lb/> been returned to me with the other
                documents,<lb/> which are properly to be in my custody. As early<lb/> as I can trace
                the matter, and procure the mau-<lb/>script, I will communicate with you
                farther.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Meanwhile, I am very respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Your obedt. &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">John M Krebs</persName>.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">In the Synod of <placeName>New York</placeName>:</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">At <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Oct. 17<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi>. 1850</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The Committee to whom had been referred<lb/> certain papers
                communicated by the <persName>Revd. Isaac<lb/> Leeser</persName>, from various
                sources, noticing the Ad-<lb/>dres to the Jews by the Synod last year, made<lb/> a
                report which was adopted, as follows, viz</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">“Whereas the documents addressed to the<lb/> Synod and referred to
                this Committee are from<lb/> individual Israelites, unauthorized to speak<lb/> for
                the Jewish Community within the bounds of<lb/> the Synod, therefore, Resolved that
                the committee<lb/> cannot recommend to the Synod to make<lb/> any official reply to
                the same.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Attest.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">John M Krebs</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Stated Clerk.</p>
        </body>
